e in this literary, jargon-free chronicle. In addition to the colorful unfolding of the social and cultural life of Mexican Los Angeles, Monroy tells a story of first-generation immigrants that provides important points of comparison for understanding other immigrant groups in the United States.Monroy shows how the transmigration of space, culture, and reality from Mexico to Los Angeles became neither wholly American nor Mexican, but México de afuera, "Mexico outside," a place where new concerns and new lives emerged from what was both old and familiar. This extremely accessible work uncovers the human stories of a dynamic immigrant population and shows the emergence of a truly transnational history and culture. Rebirth provides an integral piece of Chicano history, as well as an important element of California urban history, with the rich, synthetic portrait it gives of Mexican Los Angeles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aImmigrantsxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aImmigrantszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexican AmericansxEthnic identityxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aMexican AmericansxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aMexican AmericanszCaliforniazLos AngelesxEthnic identity. 0aMexican AmericanszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aamerican popular culture and schools.  acalifornia urban history.  acalifornian and american history.  achildren.  ahistorical fervor.  ahistory of mexicans in los angeles.  amexican boxers.  amexican community in los angeles.  amexican immigration to los angeles.  amexican los angeles.  amexico outside.  amovie stars.  aparents.  apiece of chicano history.  apoliticians.  asweeping.  avibrant.  aworkers.08iTitle is pa